rt nach sich zieht.  afunded by Deutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft (DFG)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDrugs in literature. 0aPharmacy in literature. 0aScience fictionxHistory and criticism. 0aSpeculative fictionxHistory and criticism. 4aBiopolitik. 4aFilm. 4aGender Studies. 4aKultur. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aKörper. 4aLiteratur. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aMaterialismus. 4aNeuer Materialismus. 4aPharmakologie. 4aPharmakon. 4aPhilosophie des Körpers. 4aQueer Theory. 4aStoffgeschichte. 4aSubjektivierung. 4aWirkstoff. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aActive Ingredient.  aBiopolitics.  aBody.  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aFilm.  aGender Studies.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aMaterialism.  aNew Materialism.  aPharmacology.  aPharmacon.  aPhilosophy of Body.  aQueer Theory.  aSubjectivation.  aSubstance History.2 aDeutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft (DFG)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023z978311131812708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2023z9783111024950oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839465837?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839465837423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839465837/original  a978-3-11-131812-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023b2023  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-TGPb2023